<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="623" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="25.[1976,2570,1592,2016]" box="[1976,2568,1592,1621]" pageId="25" pageNumber="623">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1976,2132,1592,1621]" pageId="25" pageNumber="623">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
Tatera lacustris Thomas &amp;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[1976,2570,1592,2016]" box="[1976,2426,1632,1661]" pageId="25" pageNumber="623">
Wroughton, 1907, 
<materialsCitation box="[2242,2426,1632,1661]" pageId="25" pageNumber="623">“Lake Chad,”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[1976,2570,1592,2016]" box="[2438,2547,1632,1661]" pageId="25" pageNumber="623">Nigeria.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[1976,2570,1592,2016]" box="[1981,2570,1671,1700]" pageId="25" pageNumber="623">Taterillus lacustris was placed in synonymy</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[1976,2570,1592,2016]" box="[1976,2568,1715,1740]" pageId="25" pageNumber="623">with 7. gracilis by D. R. Rosevear in 1969,</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[1976,2570,1592,2016]" pageId="25" pageNumber="623">while some others, including F. Petter in 1975 and C. B. Robbins in 1977, claimed its validity mainly on basis of its unique cytogenetic characters. Some new cytogenetic and morphometric analyses confirm the species as valid. Monotypic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="623" type="distribution">
